The paper discusses a model for inferring other people's goals in complex environments, which involves Bayesian inverse planning and human bounded rationality. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves behavioral experiments, which could place it in the sub-category of Cybernetics (cs.CY) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
